From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Seungwon Lee <seungwon@mulatta.io>
Date: Wed, 1 Jul 2026 12:30:00 +0900
Subject: [PATCH] store: return an empty S3 blob for empty ranges

JMAP can expose zero-byte MIME attachment parts. Downloading such a part
asks the blob store for range 0..0. The S3 backend forwards this to
rust-s3 as get_object_range(path, 0, Some(0)), but rust-s3 asserts that
start < end and panics.

Return an empty blob locally instead of sending an invalid range request.
---
 crates/store/src/backend/s3/mod.rs | 6 ++++++
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+)

diff --git a/crates/store/src/backend/s3/mod.rs b/crates/store/src/backend/s3/mod.rs
index 04283701d..e96c046a6 100644
--- a/crates/store/src/backend/s3/mod.rs
+++ b/crates/store/src/backend/s3/mod.rs
@@ -84,6 +84,12 @@ impl S3Store {
         key: &[u8],
         range: Range<usize>,
     ) -> trc::Result<Option<Vec<u8>>> {
+        // Empty MIME parts are valid. Avoid rust-s3's range assertion for
+        // get_object_range(path, 0, Some(0)).
+        if range.start >= range.end {
+            return Ok(Some(Vec::new()));
+        }
+
         let path = self.build_key(key);
         let mut retries_left = self.max_retries;
 
